Don’t overwhelm yourself with a bunch of hair products to style your wavy hair. You only need a cream or leave-in conditioner and a styling product to enhance your natural waves!

Like and share this with your wavy hair friends 🌸💗🩷

#wavyhair #wavyhairtips #wavyhairroutine #wavyhairjourney #wavyhaircommunity #wavyhaircare #wavyhairtutorial #wavyhairforbeginners #frizzyhair #poofyhair
Welcome to my little corner of ig! I’m sharing a little more of what I love with you on my page and thank you to those who continue to support my content❣️ Let’s continue to grow together! 🤍

What haircut do I get you ask? 🤔

I ask my stylist for layers to shape my hair more rounded and with curtain bangs. 💕

She starts at the base first to cut off dead ends then proceeds to the layering. 💇🏻‍♀️ 

She uses the Slide Cutting technique for layering and shaping. ✂️ 

Then she curls it with a flat iron. ✨

This haircut is great for my thick, wavy hair! 😍

Save this video to show your stylist this haircut! ❣️

#wavyhair #wavyhairroutine #hairtransformation #wavyhaircommunity #wavyhaircut

As a kid, I had curly hair, so when I started my healthy hair journey, I thought I could revive those same curls.

But what came through wasn’t curls... it was waves. I’ve come to love and embrace them!

When I first started, my hair was heat damaged, thin, and full of frizz. I didn’t know how to take care of it. All I knew was to straighten it or curl it with hot iron tools.

What I found instead was progress, not perfection.

These photos show my journey from late 2020 to 2021, and I hope they encourage anyone feeling lost in their own wavy hair journey. It’s not always easy BUT it’s worth it!
